This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) category as it deals with sentiment analysis of financial news headlines using natural language processing techniques. It could also belong to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves retrieving relevant financial news headlines for a specific company. Machine Learning (cs.LG) is another likely category as the paper uses Support Vector Regression and Bidirectional Long Short-Term Memory models to predict sentiment. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) are also possible categories as the paper involves developing and evaluating machine learning models.
